Dear colleagues (apologies for cross-posting),

We are inviting expressions of interest to host the International Statistical Ecology Conference (ISEC) in 2026. ISEC is organised every two years (typically in June or July), and it has been a very successful event to build connections across the statistical ecology community all over the world. For information about the last ISEC, held in Cape Town in 2022, please see https://www.isec2022.org/.

ISEC 2026 will be the 10th iteration of the conference, and it has been customary for past organisers to provide some guidance to prospective hosts. Conference hosts can also apply for financial support from the ISEC Foundation.

Please fill out this form to let us know that you are interested in hosting ISEC 2026: https://forms.office.com/r/8nrRGESPPL. We would like to receive applications by November 30, 2023. If you have any questions, or would like to discuss anything, you can contact the chair of the long-term planning committee (Brett McClintock, isec.ltpc at gmail.com<mailto:isec.ltpc at gmail.com>).

